  </article>
  
  <article class="post">
    <h1 class="post-title">
      <a href="/2010/06/15/Exaile-0.3.2-rc1-released/">
        Exaile 0.3.2-rc1 released
      </a>
    </h1>

    <time datetime="2010-06-15T00:00:00+00:00" class="post-date">15 Jun 2010</time>

    <p>This is a release candidate for 0.3.2. It should be stable enough for normal use, and we’ll follow it with the final version shortly.</p>

<p>A quick look at what’s new in the 0.3.2 series:</p>

<ul>
  <li>Improved support for covers embedded in ogg and flac files</li>
  <li>Gapless playback by default (via playbin2)</li>
  <li>Many dialogs replaced with gtk InfoBars</li>
  <li>Preference items that require a restart now prompt for it</li>
  <li>Vastly improved lyricsviewer plugin</li>
  <li>Drag and drop on the main cover display to set and retrieve covers</li>
  <li>Track counts in collection panel</li>
  <li>New tooltip for tray icon and minimode that displays cover and progress</li>
  <li>Custom playback sink support</li>
  <li>Display cover art when dragging from side panels</li>
  <li>Read-only support for Matroska tags…and of course, the usual assortment of bugfixes and minor enhancements.</li>
</ul>

<p>Packagers please note the version upgrades for PyGTK and PyGObject this release, 2.17 and 2.18 respectively are now mandatory.</p>

<p>You can download the release candidate from our <a href="https://launchpad.net/exaile/+download">Launchpad downloads page</a>. Please <a href="https://bugs.launchpad.net/exaile/+filebug">report any bugs you find</a> and help us make this a great release!</p>

  </article>
  
